(5, 1, '2008-09-06 22:34:24', '2008-09-07 02:34:24', '<div class="col2">\r\n<p class="lead">My name is Chris Basham. I''m a web developer and designer with the passion and knowledge to create the extraordinary. Though my <a href="#">journey</a> has only begun, let me <a href="#">share</a> with you what I''ve learned along the way.</p>\r\n\r\n<img class="alignright size-full wp-image-23" title="Self Illustration" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2008/08/profile.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="280" />\r\n<h3>About Me</h3>\r\nI''m currently a senior studying <a href="http://newmedia.iupui.edu/">New Media</a> and <a href="http://www.cs.iupui.edu/">Computer Science</a> at <a href="http://www.iupui.edu/"><abbr title="Indiana University-Purdue University of Indianapolis">IUPUI</abbr></a>. Over eight years ago I read <a href="http://www.intuitive.com/">Dave Taylor''s</a> <a href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/076453484X/"><em>Creating Cool HTML 4 Web Pages</em></a> (actually the <a href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0764532014/">first edition</a>), and since then I knew my career would reside in the Internet.\r\n\r\nFreshmen year of high school, I flipped the channel to the former <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Techtv">TechTV</a> flagship show <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Screen_Savers"><em>The Screen Savers</em></a>, introducing me to Photoshop authority <a href="http://www.bertmonroy.com/">Bert Monroy</a>; his five minute tutorial awakened me to the true potential of graphic illustration and photo manipulation. Around the same time I rented and read a 1000-page book on ActionScript 2.0 Flash programming from the local library, which coincidentally jump-started my understanding of JavaScript. The following year, I built a <a href="http://www.redhat.com/">Red Hat Linux 9</a> server (which to a novice required a hefty <a title="Red Hat Linux 9 Bible" href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0764539388">manual</a>) from spare parts and started to dabble with server-side web technologies.\r\n\r\nParalleling my early 2008 internship at Indianapolis design and web firm <a href="http://www.abeautifulquestion.com/">A Beautiful Question</a>, I burnt through the <a href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0596526954"><em>ActionScript 3.0 Cookbook</em></a> and found a new life in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Model-view-controller"><abbr title="Model View Controller">MVC</abbr></a> micro-architecture <a href="http://labs.adobe.com/wiki/index.php/Cairngorm">Cairngorm</a> building <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adobe_Flex">Flex</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adobe_Air"><abbr title="Adobe Integrated Runtime">AIR</abbr></a> applications.\r\n\r\nI''m now hoping to get back to my web roots to create purer, non-plugin based browser applications using <a href="http://www.sproutit.com/">SproutIt''s</a> JavaScript framework <a href="http://www.sproutcore.com/">SproutCore</a>.\r\n\r\nOn the non-coding side of things, I love playing <a href="http://www.nintendo.com/wii">Wii</a>, watching <a title="Hulu" href="http://www.hulu.com/">TV</a>, quoting <a title="Netflix" href="http://www.netflix.com/">movies</a>, reading <a title="Batman: Year One" href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1401207529">classic</a> <a title="Batman: The Dark Knight Returns" href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1563893428">graphic</a> <a title="Batman: The Long Halloween" href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1563894696">novels</a>, devouring <a href="http://www.bettycrocker.com/recipes/recipe.aspx?recipeID=37729">blueberry muffins</a>, joining random <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ultimate_frisbee">Ultimate Frisbee</a> games, and relaxing with a session of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disc_golf">Disc golf</a>.</div>\r\n<div class="col2">\r\n<h3>Contact</h3>\r\n<dl> <dt><span>Email</span></dt> <dd><span><a href="#">chris@bash.am</a></span></dd> <dt><span>Phone</span></dt> <dd><span>812 459 9891</span></dd> <dt><span>Location</span></dt> <dd><span><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=Indianapolis,+IN&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;z=11&amp;iwloc=addr">Indianapolis, Indiana</a></span></dd> </dl>\r\n<h3>Community</h3>\r\n<dl> <dt><span>News</span></dt> <dd><span><a class="digg" href="http://digg.com/users/chrisbasham">Digg</a></span></dd> <dt><span>Networking</span></dt> <dd><span><a class="facebook" href="http://www.facebook.com/people/Chris_Basham/27307480">Facebook</a></span></dd> <dt><span>Bookmarking</span></dt> <dd><span><a class="delicious" href="http://del.icio.us/cbasham">Del.icio.us</a></span></dd> <dt><span>Micro-Blogging</span></dt> <dd><span><a class="twitter" href="http://twitter.com/chrisbasham">Twitter</a></span></dd> <dt><span>TV &amp; Movies</span></dt> <dd><span><a class="hulu" href="http://www.hulu.com/profiles/chrisbasham/">Hulu</a></span></dd> </dl>\r\n<h3>Skills</h3>\r\n<dl> <dt><span>Languages</span></dt> <dd><span><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ActionScript">ActionScript 3</a> + <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Javascript">JavaScript</a> + <a href="http://www.php.net/"><abbr title="PHP: Hypertext Preprocessor">PHP</abbr></a> + <a href="http://www.mysql.com/">MySQL</a> + <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Xhtml"><abbr title="Extensible Hypertext Markup Language">XHTML</abbr></a> + <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cascading_Style_Sheets"><abbr title="Cascading Style Sheets">CSS</abbr></a></span> </dd> <dt><span>Technologies</span></dt> <dd><span><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ajax_%28programming%29"><abbr title="Asynchronous JavaScript and XML">Ajax</abbr></a> + <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adobe_Flex">Flex</a> + <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adobe_Air"><abbr title="Adobe Integrated Runtime">AIR</abbr></a></span></dd> <dt><span>Software</span></dt> <dd><span><a href="http://www.adobe.com/products/photoshop/">Adobe Photoshop</a> + <a href="http://www.adobe.com/products/illustrator/">Adobe Illustrator</a> + <a href="http://www.adobe.com/products/flash/">Adobe Flash</a></span></dd> </dl>\r\n<h3>Availability &amp; Resume</h3>\r\nI''m currently booked with projects through <strong>January 2009</strong>. In the meantime, download my <a href="#">resume (<abbr title="Portable Document Format">PDF</abbr>)</a>.\r\n<h3>About the Site</h3>\r\nThis site is developed as my home-base, where I can share my <a href="#">work</a> and <a href="#">thoughts</a> with the world. The site is hosted by <a href="http://www.dreamhost.com/">Dreamhost</a> and powered by <a href="http://wordpress.org/">WordPress</a>, with the theme hand-built with <a href="http://www.barebones.com/products/textwrangler/">TextWrangler</a>.</div>', 'About', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2-revision-2', '', '', '2008-09-06 22:34:24', '2008-09-07 02:34:24', '', 2, 'http://chris.bash.am/uncategorized/2-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(6, 1, '2008-09-06 23:26:43', '2008-09-07 03:26:43', '<div class="col2">\n<p class="lead">My name is Chris Basham. I''m a web developer and designer with the passion and knowledge to create the extraordinary. Though my <a href="/about/">journey</a> has only begun, let me <a href="/">share</a> with you what I''ve learned along the way.</p>\n\n<img class="alignright size-full wp-image-4" title="Self Illustration" src="http://chris.bash.am/wp-content/uploads/2008/09/profile.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="280" />\n<h3>About Me</h3>\nI''m currently a senior studying <a href="http://newmedia.iupui.edu/">New Media</a> and <a href="http://www.cs.iupui.edu/">Computer Science</a> at <a href="http://www.iupui.edu/"><abbr title="Indiana University-Purdue University of Indianapolis">IUPUI</abbr></a>. Over eight years ago I read <a href="http://www.intuitive.com/">Dave Taylor''s</a> <a href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/076453484X/"><em>Creating Cool HTML 4 Web Pages</em></a> (actually the <a href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0764532014/">first edition</a>), and since then I knew my career would reside in the Internet.\n\nFreshmen year of high school, I flipped the channel to the former <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Techtv">TechTV</a> flagship show <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Screen_Savers"><em>The Screen Savers</em></a>, introducing me to Photoshop authority <a href="http://www.bertmonroy.com/">Bert Monroy</a>; his five minute tutorial awakened me to the true potential of graphic illustration and photo manipulation. Around the same time I rented and read a 1000-page book on ActionScript 2.0 Flash programming from the local library, which coincidentally jump-started my understanding of JavaScript. The following year, I built a <a href="http://www.redhat.com/">Red Hat Linux 9</a> server (which to a novice required a hefty <a title="Red Hat Linux 9 Bible" href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0764539388">manual</a>) from spare parts and started to dabble with server-side web technologies.\n\nParalleling my early 2008 internship at Indianapolis design and web firm <a href="http://www.abeautifulquestion.com/">A Beautiful Question</a>, I burnt through the <a href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0596526954"><em>ActionScript 3.0 Cookbook</em></a> and found a new life in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Model-view-controller"><abbr title="Model View Controller">MVC</abbr></a> micro-architecture <a href="http://labs.adobe.com/wiki/index.php/Cairngorm">Cairngorm</a> building <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adobe_Flex">Flex</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adobe_Air"><abbr title="Adobe Integrated Runtime">AIR</abbr></a> applications.\n\nAs of September 2008, I''ll be interning in the <a href="http://vis.iu.edu/">Pervasive Technology Labs</a> at IUPUI, learning from the wonderful <a href="http://informatics.iupui.edu/people/baker">Dr. Polly Baker</a>. I''ll work with ActionScript 3, exploring how well the language can process video analyzation. Stay tuned.\n\nOn the non-coding side of things, I love playing <a href="http://www.nintendo.com/wii">Wii</a>, watching <a title="Hulu" href="http://www.hulu.com/">TV</a>, quoting <a title="Netflix" href="http://www.netflix.com/">movies</a>, reading <a title="Batman: Year One" href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1401207529">classic</a> <a title="Batman: The Dark Knight Returns" href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1563893428">graphic</a> <a title="Batman: The Long Halloween" href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1563894696">novels</a>, devouring <a href="http://www.bettycrocker.com/recipes/recipe.aspx?recipeID=37729">blueberry muffins</a>, joining random <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ultimate_frisbee">Ultimate Frisbee</a> games, and relaxing with a session of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disc_golf">Disc golf</a>.</div>\n<div class="col2">\n<h3>Contact</h3>\n<dl> <dt><span>Email</span></dt> <dd><span><a href="#">chris@bash.am</a></span></dd> <dt><span>Phone</span></dt> <dd><span>812 459 9891</span></dd> <dt><span>Location</span></dt> <dd><span><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=Indianapolis,+IN&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;z=11&amp;iwloc=addr">Indianapolis, Indiana</a></span></dd> </dl>\n<h3>Community</h3>\n<dl> <dt><span>News</span></dt> <dd><span><a class="digg" href="http://digg.com/users/chrisbasham">Digg</a></span></dd> <dt><span>Networking</span></dt> <dd><span><a class="facebook" href="http://www.facebook.com/people/Chris_Basham/27307480">Facebook</a></span></dd> <dt><span>Bookmarking</span></dt> <dd><span><a class="delicious" href="http://del.icio.us/cbasham">Del.icio.us</a></span></dd> <dt><span>Micro-Blogging</span></dt> <dd><span><a class="twitter" href="http://twitter.com/chrisbasham">Twitter</a></span></dd> <dt><span>TV &amp; Movies</span></dt> <dd><span><a class="hulu" href="http://www.hulu.com/profiles/chrisbasham/">Hulu</a></span></dd> </dl>\n<h3>Skills</h3>\n<dl> <dt><span>Languages</span></dt> <dd><span><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ActionScript">ActionScript 3</a> + <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Javascript">JavaScript</a> + <a href="http://www.php.net/"><abbr title="PHP: Hypertext Preprocessor">PHP</abbr></a> + <a href="http://www.mysql.com/">MySQL</a> + <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Xhtml"><abbr title="Extensible Hypertext Markup Language">XHTML</abbr></a> + <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cascading_Style_Sheets"><abbr title="Cascading Style Sheets">CSS</abbr></a></span> </dd> <dt><span>Technologies</span></dt> <dd><span><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ajax_%28programming%29"><abbr title="Asynchronous JavaScript and XML">Ajax</abbr></a> + <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adobe_Flex">Flex</a> + <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adobe_Air"><abbr title="Adobe Integrated Runtime">AIR</abbr></a></span></dd> <dt><span>Software</span></dt> <dd><span><a href="http://www.adobe.com/products/photoshop/">Adobe Photoshop</a> + <a href="http://www.adobe.com/products/illustrator/">Adobe Illustrator</a> + <a href="http://www.adobe.com/products/flash/">Adobe Flash</a></span></dd> </dl>\n<h3>Availability &amp; Resume</h3>\nI''m currently booked with projects through <strong>January 2009</strong>. In the meantime, download my <a href=''http://chris.bash.am/wp-content/uploads/2008/09/basham-resume-2008q3.pdf''>resume  (<abbr title="Portable Document Format">PDF</abbr>)</a>.\n\n<h3>About the Site</h3>\nThis site is developed as my home-base, where I can share my <a href="/">work</a> and <a href="/">thoughts</a> with the world. The site is hosted by <a href="http://www.dreamhost.com/">Dreamhost</a> and powered by <a href="http://wordpress.org/">WordPress</a>, with the theme hand-built with <a href="http://www.barebones.com/products/textwrangler/">TextWrangler</a>.</div>', 'About', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2-autosave', '', '', '2008-09-06 23:26:43', '2008-09-07 03:26:43', '', 2, 'http://chris.bash.am/uncategorized/2-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(7, 1, '2008-09-06 22:39:51', '2008-09-07 02:39:51', '', 'Chris Basham''s Resume, Q3 2008', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'basham-resume-2008q3', '', '', '2008-09-06 22:39:51', '2008-09-07 02:39:51', '', 2, 'http://chris.bash.am/wp-content/uploads/2008/09/basham-resume-2008q3.pdf', 0, 'attachment', 'application/pdf', 0),
(8, 1, '2008-09-06 22:38:20', '2008-09-07 02:38:20', '<div class="col2">\r\n<p class="lead">My name is Chris Basham. I''m a web developer and designer with the passion and knowledge to create the extraordinary. Though my <a href="#">journey</a> has only begun, let me <a href="#">share</a> with you what I''ve learned along the way.</p>\r\n\r\n<img class="alignright size-full wp-image-4" title="Self Illustration" src="http://chris.bash.am/wp-content/uploads/2008/09/profile.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="280" />\r\n<h3>About Me</h3>\r\nI''m currently a senior studying <a href="http://newmedia.iupui.edu/">New Media</a> and <a href="http://www.cs.iupui.edu/">Computer Science</a> at <a href="http://www.iupui.edu/"><abbr title="Indiana University-Purdue University of Indianapolis">IUPUI</abbr></a>. Over eight years ago I read <a href="http://www.intuitive.com/">Dave Taylor''s</a> <a href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/076453484X/"><em>Creating Cool HTML 4 Web Pages</em></a> (actually the <a href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0764532014/">first edition</a>), and since then I knew my career would reside in the Internet.\r\n\r\nFreshmen year of high school, I flipped the channel to the former <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Techtv">TechTV</a> flagship show <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Screen_Savers"><em>The Screen Savers</em></a>, introducing me to Photoshop authority <a href="http://www.bertmonroy.com/">Bert Monroy</a>; his five minute tutorial awakened me to the true potential of graphic illustration and photo manipulation. Around the same time I rented and read a 1000-page book on ActionScript 2.0 Flash programming from the local library, which coincidentally jump-started my understanding of JavaScript. The following year, I built a <a href="http://www.redhat.com/">Red Hat Linux 9</a> server (which to a novice required a hefty <a title="Red Hat Linux 9 Bible" href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0764539388">manual</a>) from spare parts and started to dabble with server-side web technologies.\r\n\r\nParalleling my early 2008 internship at Indianapolis design and web firm <a href="http://www.abeautifulquestion.com/">A Beautiful Question</a>, I burnt through the <a href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0596526954"><em>ActionScript 3.0 Cookbook</em></a> and found a new life in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Model-view-controller"><abbr title="Model View Controller">MVC</abbr></a> micro-architecture <a href="http://labs.adobe.com/wiki/index.php/Cairngorm">Cairngorm</a> building <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adobe_Flex">Flex</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adobe_Air"><abbr title="Adobe Integrated Runtime">AIR</abbr></a> applications.\r\n\r\nI''m now hoping to get back to my web roots to create purer, non-plugin based browser applications using <a href="http://www.sproutit.com/">SproutIt''s</a> JavaScript framework <a href="http://www.sproutcore.com/">SproutCore</a>.\r\n\r\nOn the non-coding side of things, I love playing <a href="http://www.nintendo.com/wii">Wii</a>, watching <a title="Hulu" href="http://www.hulu.com/">TV</a>, quoting <a title="Netflix" href="http://www.netflix.com/">movies</a>, reading <a title="Batman: Year One" href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1401207529">classic</a> <a title="Batman: The Dark Knight Returns" href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1563893428">graphic</a> <a title="Batman: The Long Halloween" href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1563894696">novels</a>, devouring <a href="http://www.bettycrocker.com/recipes/recipe.aspx?recipeID=37729">blueberry muffins</a>, joining random <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ultimate_frisbee">Ultimate Frisbee</a> games, and relaxing with a session of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disc_golf">Disc golf</a>.</div>\r\n<div class="col2">\r\n<h3>Contact</h3>\r\n<dl> <dt><span>Email</span></dt> <dd><span><a href="#">chris@bash.am</a></span></dd> <dt><span>Phone</span></dt> <dd><span>812 459 9891</span></dd> <dt><span>Location</span></dt> <dd><span><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=Indianapolis,+IN&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;z=11&amp;iwloc=addr">Indianapolis, Indiana</a></span></dd> </dl>\r\n<h3>Community</h3>\r\n<dl> <dt><span>News</span></dt> <dd><span><a class="digg" href="http://digg.com/users/chrisbasham">Digg</a></span></dd> <dt><span>Networking</span></dt> <dd><span><a class="facebook" href="http://www.facebook.com/people/Chris_Basham/27307480">Facebook</a></span></dd> <dt><span>Bookmarking</span></dt> <dd><span><a class="delicious" href="http://del.icio.us/cbasham">Del.icio.us</a></span></dd> <dt><span>Micro-Blogging</span></dt> <dd><span><a class="twitter" href="http://twitter.com/chrisbasham">Twitter</a></span></dd> <dt><span>TV &amp; Movies</span></dt> <dd><span><a class="hulu" href="http://www.hulu.com/profiles/chrisbasham/">Hulu</a></span></dd> </dl>\r\n<h3>Skills</h3>\r\n<dl> <dt><span>Languages</span></dt> <dd><span><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ActionScript">ActionScript 3</a> + <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Javascript">JavaScript</a> + <a href="http://www.php.net/"><abbr title="PHP: Hypertext Preprocessor">PHP</abbr></a> + <a href="http://www.mysql.com/">MySQL</a> + <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Xhtml"><abbr title="Extensible Hypertext Markup Language">XHTML</abbr></a> + <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cascading_Style_Sheets"><abbr title="Cascading Style Sheets">CSS</abbr></a></span> </dd> <dt><span>Technologies</span></dt> <dd><span><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ajax_%28programming%29"><abbr title="Asynchronous JavaScript and XML">Ajax</abbr></a> + <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adobe_Flex">Flex</a> + <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adobe_Air"><abbr title="Adobe Integrated Runtime">AIR</abbr></a></span></dd> <dt><span>Software</span></dt> <dd><span><a href="http://www.adobe.com/products/photoshop/">Adobe Photoshop</a> + <a href="http://www.adobe.com/products/illustrator/">Adobe Illustrator</a> + <a href="http://www.adobe.com/products/flash/">Adobe Flash</a></span></dd> </dl>\r\n<h3>Availability &amp; Resume</h3>\r\nI''m currently booked with projects through <strong>January 2009</strong>. In the meantime, download my <a href="#">resume (<abbr title="Portable Document Format">PDF</abbr>)</a>.\r\n<h3>About the Site</h3>\r\nThis site is developed as my home-base, where I can share my <a href="#">work</a> and <a href="#">thoughts</a> with the world. The site is hosted by <a href="http://www.dreamhost.com/">Dreamhost</a> and powered by <a href="http://wordpress.org/">WordPress</a>, with the theme hand-built with <a href="http://www.barebones.com/products/textwrangler/">TextWrangler</a>.</div>', 'About', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2-revision-3', '', '', '2008-09-06 22:38:20', '2008-09-07 02:38:20', '', 2, 'http://chris.bash.am/uncategorized/2-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(9, 1, '2008-09-06 22:41:22', '2008-09-07 02:41:22', '<div class="col2">\r\n<p class="lead">My name is Chris Basham. I''m a web developer and designer with the passion and knowledge to create the extraordinary. Though my <a href="#">journey</a> has only begun, let me <a href="#">share</a> with you what I''ve learned along the way.</p>\r\n\r\n<img class="alignright size-full wp-image-4" title="Self Illustration" src="http://chris.bash.am/wp-content/uploads/2008/09/profile.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="280" />\r\n<h3>About Me</h3>\r\nI''m currently a senior studying <a href="http://newmedia.iupui.edu/">New Media</a> and <a href="http://www.cs.iupui.edu/">Computer Science</a> at <a href="http://www.iupui.edu/"><abbr title="Indiana University-Purdue University of Indianapolis">IUPUI</abbr></a>. Over eight years ago I read <a href="http://www.intuitive.com/">Dave Taylor''s</a> <a href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/076453484X/"><em>Creating Cool HTML 4 Web Pages</em></a> (actually the <a href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0764532014/">first edition</a>), and since then I knew my career would reside in the Internet.\r\n\r\nFreshmen year of high school, I flipped the channel to the former <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Techtv">TechTV</a> flagship show <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Screen_Savers"><em>The Screen Savers</em></a>, introducing me to Photoshop authority <a href="http://www.bertmonroy.com/">Bert Monroy</a>; his five minute tutorial awakened me to the true potential of graphic illustration and photo manipulation. Around the same time I rented and read a 1000-page book on ActionScript 2.0 Flash programming from the local library, which coincidentally jump-started my understanding of JavaScript. The following year, I built a <a href="http://www.redhat.com/">Red Hat Linux 9</a> server (which to a novice required a hefty <a title="Red Hat Linux 9 Bible" href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0764539388">manual</a>) from spare parts and started to dabble with server-side web technologies.\r\n\r\nParalleling my early 2008 internship at Indianapolis design and web firm <a href="http://www.abeautifulquestion.com/">A Beautiful Question</a>, I burnt through the <a href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0596526954"><em>ActionScript 3.0 Cookbook</em></a> and found a new life in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Model-view-controller"><abbr title="Model View Controller">MVC</abbr></a> micro-architecture <a href="http://labs.adobe.com/wiki/index.php/Cairngorm">Cairngorm</a> building <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adobe_Flex">Flex</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adobe_Air"><abbr title="Adobe Integrated Runtime">AIR</abbr></a> applications.\r\n\r\nI''m now hoping to get back to my web roots to create purer, non-plugin based browser applications using <a href="http://www.sproutit.com/">SproutIt''s</a> JavaScript framework <a href="http://www.sproutcore.com/">SproutCore</a>.\r\n\r\nOn the non-coding side of things, I love playing <a href="http://www.nintendo.com/wii">Wii</a>, watching <a title="Hulu" href="http://www.hulu.com/">TV</a>, quoting <a title="Netflix" href="http://www.netflix.com/">movies</a>, reading <a title="Batman: Year One" href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1401207529">classic</a> <a title="Batman: The Dark Knight Returns" href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1563893428">graphic</a> <a title="Batman: The Long Halloween" href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1563894696">novels</a>, devouring <a href="http://www.bettycrocker.com/recipes/recipe.aspx?recipeID=37729">blueberry muffins</a>, joining random <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ultimate_frisbee">Ultimate Frisbee</a> games, and relaxing with a session of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disc_golf">Disc golf</a>.</div>\r\n<div class="col2">\r\n<h3>Contact</h3>\r\n<dl> <dt><span>Email</span></dt> <dd><span><a href="#">chris@bash.am</a></span></dd> <dt><span>Phone</span></dt> <dd><span>812 459 9891</span></dd> <dt><span>Location</span></dt> <dd><span><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=Indianapolis,+IN&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;z=11&amp;iwloc=addr">Indianapolis, Indiana</a></span></dd> </dl>\r\n<h3>Community</h3>\r\n<dl> <dt><span>News</span></dt> <dd><span><a class="digg" href="http://digg.com/users/chrisbasham">Digg</a></span></dd> <dt><span>Networking</span></dt> <dd><span><a class="facebook" href="http://www.facebook.com/people/Chris_Basham/27307480">Facebook</a></span></dd> <dt><span>Bookmarking</span></dt> <dd><span><a class="delicious" href="http://del.icio.us/cbasham">Del.icio.us</a></span></dd> <dt><span>Micro-Blogging</span></dt> <dd><span><a class="twitter" href="http://twitter.com/chrisbasham">Twitter</a></span></dd> <dt><span>TV &amp; Movies</span></dt> <dd><span><a class="hulu" href="http://www.hulu.com/profiles/chrisbasham/">Hulu</a></span></dd> </dl>\r\n<h3>Skills</h3>\r\n<dl> <dt><span>Languages</span></dt> <dd><span><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ActionScript">ActionScript 3</a> + <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Javascript">JavaScript</a> + <a href="http://www.php.net/"><abbr title="PHP: Hypertext Preprocessor">PHP</abbr></a> + <a href="http://www.mysql.com/">MySQL</a> + <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Xhtml"><abbr title="Extensible Hypertext Markup Language">XHTML</abbr></a> + <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cascading_Style_Sheets"><abbr title="Cascading Style Sheets">CSS</abbr></a></span> </dd> <dt><span>Technologies</span></dt> <dd><span><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ajax_%28programming%29"><abbr title="Asynchronous JavaScript and XML">Ajax</abbr></a> + <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adobe_Flex">Flex</a> + <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adobe_Air"><abbr title="Adobe Integrated Runtime">AIR</abbr></a></span></dd> <dt><span>Software</span></dt> <dd><span><a href="http://www.adobe.com/products/photoshop/">Adobe Photoshop</a> + <a href="http://www.adobe.com/products/illustrator/">Adobe Illustrator</a> + <a href="http://www.adobe.com/products/flash/">Adobe Flash</a></span></dd> </dl>\r\n<h3>Availability &amp; Resume</h3>\r\nI''m currently booked with projects through <strong>January 2009</strong>. In the meantime, download my <a href=''http://chris.bash.am/wp-content/uploads/2008/09/basham-resume-2008q3.pdf''>resume  (<abbr title="Portable Document Format">PDF</abbr>)</a>.\r\n\r\n<h3>About the Site</h3>\r\nThis site is developed as my home-base, where I can share my <a href="#">work</a> and <a href="#">thoughts</a> with the world. The site is hosted by <a href="http://www.dreamhost.com/">Dreamhost</a> and powered by <a href="http://wordpress.org/">WordPress</a>, with the theme hand-built with <a href="http://www.barebones.com/products/textwrangler/">TextWrangler</a>.</div>', 'About', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2-revision-4', '', '', '2008-09-06 22:41:22', '2008-09-07 02:41:22', '', 2, 'http://chris.bash.am/uncategorized/2-revision-4/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`, `post_author`, `post_date`, `post_date_gmt`, `post_content`, `post_title`, `post_category`, `post_excerpt`, `post_status`, `comment_status`, `ping_status`, `post_password`, `post_name`, `to_ping`, `pinged`, `post_modified`, `post_modified_gmt`, `post_content_filtered`, `post_parent`, `guid`, `menu_order`, `post_type`, `post_mime_type`, `comment_count`) VALUES
(10, 1, '2008-09-06 22:42:14', '2008-09-07 02:42:14', '<div class="col2">\r\n<p class="lead">My name is Chris Basham. I''m a web developer and designer with the passion and knowledge to create the extraordinary. Though my <a href="#">journey</a> has only begun, let me <a href="#">share</a> with you what I''ve learned along the way.</p>\r\n\r\n<img class="alignright size-full wp-image-4" title="Self Illustration" src="http://chris.bash.am/wp-content/uploads/2008/09/profile.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="280" />\r\n<h3>About Me</h3>\r\nI''m currently a senior studying <a href="http://newmedia.iupui.edu/">New Media</a> and <a href="http://www.cs.iupui.edu/">Computer Science</a> at <a href="http://www.iupui.edu/"><abbr title="Indiana University-Purdue University of Indianapolis">IUPUI</abbr></a>. Over eight years ago I read <a href="http://www.intuitive.com/">Dave Taylor''s</a> <a href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/076453484X/"><em>Creating Cool HTML 4 Web Pages</em></a> (actually the <a href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0764532014/">first edition</a>), and since then I knew my career would reside in the Internet.\r\n\r\nFreshmen year of high school, I flipped the channel to the former <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Techtv">TechTV</a> flagship show <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Screen_Savers"><em>The Screen Savers</em></a>, introducing me to Photoshop authority <a href="http://www.bertmonroy.com/">Bert Monroy</a>; his five minute tutorial awakened me to the true potential of graphic illustration and photo manipulation. Around the same time I rented and read a 1000-page book on ActionScript 2.0 Flash programming from the local library, which coincidentally jump-started my understanding of JavaScript. The following year, I built a <a href="http://www.redhat.com/">Red Hat Linux 9</a> server (which to a novice required a hefty <a title="Red Hat Linux 9 Bible" href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0764539388">manual</a>) from spare parts and started to dabble with server-side web technologies.\r\n\r\nParalleling my early 2008 internship at Indianapolis design and web firm <a href="http://www.abeautifulquestion.com/">A Beautiful Question</a>, I burnt through the <a href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0596526954"><em>ActionScript 3.0 Cookbook</em></a> and found a new life in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Model-view-controller"><abbr title="Model View Controller">MVC</abbr></a> micro-architecture <a href="http://labs.adobe.com/wiki/index.php/Cairngorm">Cairngorm</a> building <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adobe_Flex">Flex</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adobe_Air"><abbr title="Adobe Integrated Runtime">AIR</abbr></a> applications.\r\n\r\nI''m now hoping to get back to my web roots to create purer, non-plugin based browser applications using <a href="http://www.sproutit.com/">SproutIt''s</a> JavaScript framework <a href="http://www.sproutcore.com/">SproutCore</a>.\r\n\r\nOn the non-coding side of things, I love playing <a href="http://www.nintendo.com/wii">Wii</a>, watching <a title="Hulu" href="http://www.hulu.com/">TV</a>, quoting <a title="Netflix" href="http://www.netflix.com/">movies</a>, reading <a title="Batman: Year One" href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1401207529">classic</a> <a title="Batman: The Dark Knight Returns" href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1563893428">graphic</a> <a title="Batman: The Long Halloween" href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1563894696">novels</a>, devouring <a href="http://www.bettycrocker.com/recipes/recipe.aspx?recipeID=37729">blueberry muffins</a>, joining random <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ultimate_frisbee">Ultimate Frisbee</a> games, and relaxing with a session of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disc_golf">Disc golf</a>.</div>\r\n<div class="col2">\r\n<h3>Contact</h3>\r\n<dl> <dt><span>Email</span></dt> <dd><span><a href="#">chris@bash.am</a></span></dd> <dt><span>Phone</span></dt> <dd><span>812 459 9891</span></dd> <dt><span>Location</span></dt> <dd><span><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=Indianapolis,+IN&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;z=11&amp;iwloc=addr">Indianapolis, Indiana</a></span></dd> </dl>\r\n<h3>Community</h3>\r\n<dl> <dt><span>News</span></dt> <dd><span><a class="digg" href="http://digg.com/users/chrisbasham">Digg</a></span></dd> <dt><span>Networking</span></dt> <dd><span><a class="facebook" href="http://www.facebook.com/people/Chris_Basham/27307480">Facebook</a></span></dd> <dt><span>Bookmarking</span></dt> <dd><span><a class="delicious" href="http://del.icio.us/cbasham">Del.icio.us</a></span></dd> <dt><span>Micro-Blogging</span></dt> <dd><span><a class="twitter" href="http://twitter.com/chrisbasham">Twitter</a></span></dd> <dt><span>TV &amp; Movies</span></dt> <dd><span><a class="hulu" href="http://www.hulu.com/profiles/chrisbasham/">Hulu</a></span></dd> </dl>\r\n<h3>Skills</h3>\r\n<dl> <dt><span>Languages</span></dt> <dd><span><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ActionScript">ActionScript 3</a> + <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Javascript">JavaScript</a> + <a href="http://www.php.net/"><abbr title="PHP: Hypertext Preprocessor">PHP</abbr></a> + <a href="http://www.mysql.com/">MySQL</a> + <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Xhtml"><abbr title="Extensible Hypertext Markup Language">XHTML</abbr></a> + <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cascading_Style_Sheets"><abbr title="Cascading Style Sheets">CSS</abbr></a></span> </dd> <dt><span>Technologies</span></dt> <dd><span><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ajax_%28programming%29"><abbr title="Asynchronous JavaScript and XML">Ajax</abbr></a> + <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adobe_Flex">Flex</a> + <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adobe_Air"><abbr title="Adobe Integrated Runtime">AIR</abbr></a></span></dd> <dt><span>Software</span></dt> <dd><span><a href="http://www.adobe.com/products/photoshop/">Adobe Photoshop</a> + <a href="http://www.adobe.com/products/illustrator/">Adobe Illustrator</a> + <a href="http://www.adobe.com/products/flash/">Adobe Flash</a></span></dd> </dl>\r\n<h3>Availability &amp; Resume</h3>\r\nI''m currently booked with projects through <strong>January 2009</strong>. In the meantime, download my <a href=''http://chris.bash.am/wp-content/uploads/2008/09/basham-resume-2008q3.pdf''>resume  (<abbr title="Portable Document Format">PDF</abbr>)</a>.\r\n\r\n<h3>About the Site</h3>\r\nThis site is developed as my home-base, where I can share my <a href="/">work</a> and <a href="/">thoughts</a> with the world. The site is hosted by <a href="http://www.dreamhost.com/">Dreamhost</a> and powered by <a href="http://wordpress.org/">WordPress</a>, with the theme hand-built with <a href="http://www.barebones.com/products/textwrangler/">TextWrangler</a>.</div>', 'About', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2-revision-5', '', '', '2008-09-06 22:42:14', '2008-09-07 02:42:14', '', 2, 'http://chris.bash.am/uncategorized/2-revision-5/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
